data.chText: 驱散，消除（尤指感觉或信仰）
data.enText: to make sth, especially a feeling or belief, go away or disappear

data.chText: 他的发言消除了人们对他身体健康的担心。
data.enText: His speech dispelled any fears about his health.

simple_means.memory_skill: dis 分散 + pel 驱动；推 → 推开 → 驱散

tr: used both with concrete and metaphoric meanings
example: The supermarket had to turn back many disappointed customers

tr: to cause to separate and go in different directions
example: She waved her hand and scattered the crowds

value.def: To dispel an idea or feeling that people have means to stop them having it.

example.ex: The President is attempting to dispel the notion that he has neglected the economy.
example.tran: 有人认为总统忽视了经济，总统正试图消除这种看法。

rootsaffixes.indicate: = to drive, to push 驱动；推
rootsaffixes.title: pel, puls
